description:
Build the inline-failure rendering surface in the FE. Today plugin-actions.ts only logs failures to DevTools via console.error (a temporary diagnostic). The user-visible banner carries only the count summary ('1 steering failed · 8 agents failed') — the per-item error chains the backend sends are not surfaced inline.

The new FailedAgent wire shape from PR #113 is what the inline UI should consume. The plugin-actions.ts comment block near the consumer site documents the target switch shape:

  switch (entry.kind) {
    case 'agent': return renderAgent(entry.name, entry.source_path, entry.error);
    case 'unparseable_agent': return renderUnparseable(entry.source_path, entry.error);
    case 'companion_bundle': return renderBundle(entry.plugin, entry.conflicts, entry.error);
    default: { const _exhaustive: never = entry; throw new Error(...); }
  }

Pair the switch with a value-position _AssertExhaustive guard per CLAUDE.md discriminator-pushdown discipline (see _PLUGIN_ACTION_VALUES + _AssertPluginActionExhaustive in stores/plugin-updates.ts as the canonical precedent).

Target shape: InstalledTab.svelte's runPluginRemove per-failure <details> panel.

COUPLING: when F3 ships, the plugin-actions.ts console.error diagnostic block must be removed IN THE SAME COMMIT as the inline UI lands. A separate cleanup PR risks stripping the diagnostic before F3 is ready, losing per-item failure visibility entirely. (Tracked as kiro-5qcb, blocked by this issue.)

Why deferred from PR #113: UI work is a separate concern from the wire-format change. Bundling would force the PR to also touch InstalledTab.svelte + component testing infrastructure.

See: docs/plans/2026-05-09-failed-agent-discriminator-design.md F3, crates/kiro-control-center/src/lib/plugin-actions.ts (forward-looking switch comment), crates/kiro-control-center/src/lib/components/InstalledTab.svelte (target shape)
